<br>
PoP introduced ultra-high damage mobs as a response to mob hps inflation / increasing combat duration. High DPS, shorter fights. For the most part, this worked out ok, (though solo melee might disagree).<br>
<br>
Problem is, when a player can turn the augmented DPS of these PoP mobs against other mobs...you're doing something which I bet Sony never foresaw (correctly). High DPS, short-duration fights work perfectly for charmers. That's what is &quot;new&quot; here.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I don't like the fix. It doesn't deter what most people were bitching about (ENC's taking out &quot;raid-level&quot; mobs) all it does is make charming less desireable for experience.<br>
<br>
Should have left everything the same, and just halved the DPS of charmed mobs.<br>
